y of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: variant of   Lovell  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Lovell","meanings":["English: nickname from Anglo-Norman French <i>lovel</i> ‘wolf cub’, a diminutive of <i>lou</i>, <i>love</i> ‘wolf’. Compare   Love   and   Low  ."]}]},{"name":"Muriel","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of Celtic origin (  see  Muireall   ). Forms of the name are found in Breton as well as in Irish and Scottish Gaelic, and in the form   Meriel   it was in use in the heart of England in the Middle Ages. The surname <i>Merrill</i> is derived from it. As <i>Muriel</i> it was at first used mainly in Scotland, but became more widely popular during the first half of the 20th century. Since then it has fallen from favour again."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705192,"age":0,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":9,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Muriel Lovel was born in 1328, in Castle Cary, Somerset, England, her father, James Lovell, was 23 and her mother, Isabella la Zouche, was 10. She married Nicholas Saint Maur about 1340. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died before 1361."},"et":{"1328–before 1361":"1328–enne 1361","1328–1361":"1328–1361","1335–Male":"1335–Surnud","1316–1361":"1316–1361","1350–1361":"1350–1361","1355–1401":"1355–1401","1306–1342":"1306–1342","1318–1387":"1318–1387",